      "### Town Planning and Architecture of IVC\n\nThe Indus Valley Civilization (IVC) is renowned for its grid-pattern street layout and advanced municipal planning. Streets cut each other at right angles, dividing the town into rectangular blocks.\n\n* **Citadel and Lower Town**: Most cities were divided into a fortified Citadel on the west (housing public buildings, ruling class) and a Lower Town on the east (housing common citizens).\n* **Building Materials**: Burnt bricks of standard ratio (4:2:1) were used. Stone was rarely used, except in Dholavira.\n* **Drainage System**: Excellent covered drainage network. Every house had its own soak pit connected to street drains, showing high sanitation standards.",
