      "### Multi-dimensional Causes of the Revolt\n\nThe rebellion of 1857 was not a sudden explosion, but the culmination of accumulating grievances against British rule:\n\n* **Economic Causes**: Heavy land revenue systems (Permanent Settlement, Ryotwari, Mahalwari), destruction of traditional Indian handicraft industry, drain of wealth.\n* **Political Causes**: 'Doctrine of Lapse' (Dalhousie) annexed Satara, Jhansi, Nagpur. Annexation of Awadh (1856) on grounds of misgovernment deeply hurt sepoy sentiments.\n* **Social & Religious Causes**: English education, abolition of Sati (1829), Hindu Widows' Remarriage Act (1856), tax on temple and mosque lands.\n* **Military Causes**: Introduction of Enfield rifles (greased cartridges made of beef and pork fat), lower pay for Indian sepoys compared to British counterparts.",
