      "### Classification of DPSPs\n\nThough not classified in the text, they are conceptually grouped into three categories:\n\n* **Socialistic Principles**: Aim at social and economic justice (e.g., Art 38 - promote welfare, minimize inequalities; Art 39 - secure livelihood, prevent concentration of wealth; Art 39A - equal justice and free legal aid; Art 41 - right to work, education).\n* **Gandhian Principles**: Based on Gandhi's program of reconstruction (e.g., Art 40 - organize village panchayats; Art 43 - promote cottage industries; Art 43B - voluntary formation of cooperatives; Art 46 - promote SC/ST interests; Art 47 - ban intoxicating drinks).\n* **Liberal-Intellectual Principles**: Reflect modern liberalism (e.g., Art 44 - Uniform Civil Code; Art 45 - early childhood care/education; Art 48 - organize agriculture/animal husbandry; Art 48A - protect environment/wildlife; Art 50 - separate judiciary from executive; Art 51 - promote international peace)."
