      "### Institutional Safeguards in India\n\nIndia has established multiple agencies to counter cyber vulnerabilities:\n\n* **Information Technology Act, 2000**: Core legal framework. Section 66A was struck down (Shreya Singhal case), but provisions for cyber-crimes and data liability remain active.\n* **CERT-In (Indian Computer Emergency Response Team)**: National nodal agency for responding to computer security incidents under the Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology (MeitY).\n* **NCIIPC (National Critical Information Infrastructure Protection Centre)**: Established under Section 70A of IT Act to protect critical sectors (Power, Transport, Banking, Telecom, Strategic, Govt).\n* **National Cyber Security Policy 2013**: Aims to build a secure cyberspace, train 5 lakh professionals, and create coordination hubs (like Cyber Swachhta Kendra)."
