      "### Definition, Essence, and Dimensions of Ethics\n\nEthics is a set of systematic standards that guide human actions, helping individuals distinguish between right and wrong behavior.\n\n* **Essence of Ethics**: Involves moral choice, duty, value systems, and the common good. It is not law (which is outer enforcement) but inner moral conviction.\n* **Determinants of Ethics in Human Actions**:\n  - *Object of Action*: What is being done? (e.g., lying vs truth-telling).\n  - *Circumstance*: Context of the action (e.g., lying to save a life vs lying for personal gain).\n  - *Motive/Intent*: Goal of the agent (e.g., public welfare vs greed).\n* **Consequences of Ethics**: Promotes social harmony, trust in administration, preservation of environment, and self-actualization.",
